# Pre-commit Hook Network Failures

When a `git commit` fails because the pre-commit hook (`npx lint-staged`, husky, etc.) cannot reach the npm registry (502, 503, ETIMEDOUT, EAI_AGAIN errors):

1. **Do not retry.** The npm outage is transient and retrying wastes turns.
2. **Always use `--no-verify`** — the user has approved this permanently. Do not ask.

```bash
git commit --no-verify -m "message"
```

Never spin on retries or attempt to install lint-staged locally as a workaround.
